cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SE 

This paper deals with the classification of malware using machine learning techniques, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of Random Forest algorithm for classification suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The conversion of malware binary into an image implies the use of computer vision techniques (cs.CV). Finally, the study involves the development of a new method for malware detection, which could also fall under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
